verse.lines:
{lang-eng}Majestic sweetness sits enthroned
Upon the Savior’s brow;
His head with radiant glories crowned,
His lips with grace o’erflow.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}No mortal can with Him compare
Among the sons of men;
Fairer is He than all the fair
That fill the heavenly train.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}He saw me plunged in deep distress,
and flew to my relief;
for me He bore the shameful cross,
and carried all my grief.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}To Him I owe my life and breath,
And all the joys I have;
He makes me triumph over death,
And saves me from the grave.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}To God, the Father, my abode,
He brings my weary feet;
Shows me the glories of my God,
And makes my joys complete.{/lang-eng}
